    "created_at": "2014-08-05T18:03:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-05T18:03:04Z",
    "body": "I would expect the empty arguments to be passed through as significant argument position. I ran into this in cargo because `Command::new(\"rustdoc\").arg(\"--test-args\").arg(\"\")` passed on unix but on windows it would try to consume the next argument for the test args.\n\nIt looks like to fix this we just need to alter [this condition](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/libnative/io/process.rs#L482) to see if the argument is 0-length, and if so we quote it. Libuv already does [something similar](https://github.com/joyent/libuv/blob/master/src/win/process.c#L450-L451).\n\nI'm investigating a fix for libgreen, it looks like it should be working...\n",
